I’m so grateful that our sweet little princess is here with us! Many of you asked about the birth story, so here goes! 

At the start of the 3rd trimester, I began having cramping, which is normal. I had a similar experience with my first pregnancy, going into L&D for preterm labor contractions at 27 wks due to dehydration. With Myra, I was having a hard time determining Braxton Hicks from real labor contractions. Since I was running after a toddler this time around, I just assumed it was normal pregnancy pain. 

At 34 wks I started having contractions about 5 mins apart, so Malick & I rushed to the hospital. Luckily, I wasn’t dilated. After giving me fluids, they sent me home saying it was Braxton Hicks, but no way to differentiate from real labor contractions.

Not dilated at my 35 week checkup, I went home thinking that Myra wouldn’t come for another 4 wks. That night, my contractions started again as they did every night, so I made nothing of it. They continued throughout the night making it impossible to sleep, but this time with extreme lower back pain. We’d gone to L&D the weekend before for a false alarm, so we couldn’t help but wonder, was this any different? So many questions ran through my mind, but Malick insisted we go just to be safe.

When we got to L&D that morning, I was 5cm dilated- Malick & I were in shock! They gave me a steroid shot to mature the baby’s lungs in case I went into labor. The plan was to monitor me overnight because my blood pressure was fluctuating, but they said I could stay 5cm dilated for the remainder of the pregnancy. In the middle of the night, my contractions worsened & shortly after that my water broke. I was in active labor for 48 hours before Myra was born, however, the actual labor part was quicker this time around. I only had to push for roughly 30 mins before she made her grand debut at 11:36am on 11/21/22!

I wanted to share Myra’s birth story in full transparency for any mamas that may benefit! We are extremely grateful she is here, happy, healthy, & safe! It’s important to know the signs and symptoms of preterm labor beforehand. 

We are so in love with our sweet Myra and hardly remember life without her! 🙏🏽

Happy February, Instafam! 🤍 I see a lot of new faces here, so allow me to re-introduce myself and share some fun facts about me! 

	•	My name is Farheen, pronounced FAR like far far away and heen like bean, but with an H. People have butchered my name my entire life and I never really would correct them, but I do now. It’s my name and my identity and want it to be known. The only people I won’t correct are the Starbucks employees, I get a kick out of what they write. 😂
	•	Mommy to a very energetic 2 and a half year old boy named Kayden, and a 2 month old baby girl, Myra! 👦🏻👶🏻
	•	Been married to my best friend and high school sweetheart for 5 years! ❤️
 • My family is my world 🌎
	•	Live in the northwest suburbs of Chicago. I’ve lived in the city as well and loved the hustle the buste for a while. Once we were planning to have kids, we decided the burbs were a better option for us. 🌃 
	•	Was born in Karachi, Pakistan and moved to Chicago when I was a year old. Lived here ever since! 🇵🇰🇺🇸 
	•	Both of my parents are Bengali 🇧🇩 
	•	I am the middle child 🧍🏽‍♀️💃🏻🧍🏽‍♀️
	•	Birthday is July 8th! Where my 🦀♋️ at?
	•	I have two sisters and they are also my best friends! Very close to both of them and talk to them about anything and everything. 😘
	•	Before blogging full-time, I used to be a research and development Scientist working for a pharmaceutical company. 🔬 
	•	I transitioned to full-time blogger after Kayden was born. 💻
	•	Love fashion, beauty, and interior design. 👗💄🛋️
	•	My husband and I have traveled the world and we are so grateful for our pre-baby adventures! Highly recommend traveling before kids if you’re able because it’s such a great way to see the world and take time for yourself! Check them out in my highlights ✈️
	•	My favorite food is pizza and fav chips are Funyuns (flamin’ hot & regular) 🍕
 • Favorite TV show is The Office and the Kardashians 📺
	•	Started blogging as a hobby 9 years ago while I was doing some personal styling and so glad I took the leap. I absolutely LOVE what I do! 🤍

I’d love to get to know you all, as well! So please introduce yourself and tell me a fact about you! 😘

A beautiful night for a beautiful cause 💜 @alzassociation. We attend the Alzheimer’s Association Gala every year in honor of Malick’s grandmother who passed from it. I’ve seen first hand how it can affect the person living with it, as well as the family caring for them. 

A few facts about Alzheimer’s that I didn’t know and thought I’d share with you all:

• More than 6 million Americans are living with Alzheimer’s
• It kills more people than breast cancer and prostate cancer combined
• 1 in 3 seniors dies with Alzheimer’s or another dementia
• The lifetime risk at age 45 is 1 in 5 women and 1 in 10 men
• Almost two-thirds of Americans with Alzheimer's are women

To learn more and to see how you can help the fight, visit Alz.org #AlzheimersinAmerica

Growing up, my family had challenging times financially and I vividly remember the first time I saw a Barbie doll. I was about 5 years old. One of my dad's frequent customers at the time had given him a huge bag full of Barbie dolls, and my dad brought it home for my sisters and I. We were SO happy and loved playing with those very Barbies for many years. We didn’t have a Ken at the time, so we took scissors and cut one of the Barbie’s hair to have a makeshift “Ken” doll. Those Barbie dolls were such a formative part of my childhood and with the Barbie movie released today, I can’t help but reminisce on the struggles my parents overcame to and how far we’ve come since. To think where we are now, makes me so grateful for how hard my parents worked to spare us from their difficult reality and let our imagination run free in our little Barbie world. 🙏🏽 

Just wanted to share a little story time. Even though I’ve missed every Barbie event in the city (motherhood takes priority these days 🤍), I am still excited to celebrate the @barbiethemovie coming out today! In honor of that, here is me in a pink, feathered blazer! 💞
